cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with text compression and language modeling using BERT. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a fully unsupervised model for text compression. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper uses a deep learning model (BERT) for language modeling. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as text compression can be useful for improving search engine efficiency. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on neural network architecture design or evolutionary algorithms.
